# üöÄ LootGlitch Deployment Guide

## üìã Pre-Deployment Checklist

### 1. Telegram Bot Setup ‚úÖ
- [ ] Create bot via @BotFather
- [ ] Save bot token
- [ ] Get your Telegram ID (use @userinfobot)
- [ ] Create group/channel for database storage
- [ ] Get group ID
- [ ] Add bot to group as admin

### 2. Domain Setup (Optional)
- [ ] Purchase domain (lootglitch.me)
- [ ] Configure DNS settings
- [ ] Point to Render deployment

### 3. Adsterra Account
- [ ] Sign up at adsterra.com
- [ ] Create banner ad (728x90)
- [ ] Create SmartLink
- [ ] Save ad IDs

## üåê Deployment on Render.com

### Step 1: Create Account
1. Go to [render.com](https://render.com)
2. Sign up with GitHub

### Step 2: New Web Service
1. Click "New +"
2. Select "Web Service"
3. Connect GitHub repository

### Step 3: Configure Service
```
Name: lootglitch
Environment: Node
Region: Choose closest to target audience
Branch: main
Build Command: npm install
Start Command: npm start
```

### Step 4: Environment Variables
Add these in Render dashboard:

```env
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000

# Telegram (REQUIRED)
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
TELEGRAM_ADMIN_ID=your_telegram_id_here
TELEGRAM_GROUP_ID=your_group_id_here

# Site Configuration
SITE_URL=https://your-app.onrender.com
SITE_NAME=LootGlitch

# Adsterra (Optional - add later)
ADSTERRA_BANNER_ID=your_banner_id
ADSTERRA_SMARTLINK_ID=your_smartlink_id

# Revenue Settings
BASE_CPM=2.5
REFERRAL_MULTIPLIER=0.15
```

### Step 5: Deploy
1. Click "Create Web Service"
2. Wait for build to complete (2-5 minutes)
3. Your app will be live at: `https://lootglitch.onrender.com`

## üéØ Post-Deployment Tasks

### 1. Test Telegram Bot
```
1. Open Telegram
2. Start chat with your bot
3. Send /stats command
4. Should receive statistics
```

### 2. Test Registration
```
1. Visit your site
2. Click user icon
3. Register new account
4. Check Telegram bot for confirmation
```

### 3. Test Claim Flow
```
1. Login to site
2. Select a game
3. Choose reward amount
4. Click claim
5. Verify troll popup appears
6. Test referral link generation
```

### 4. Configure Custom Domain (Optional)

#### On Render:
1. Go to Settings
2. Click "Custom Domain"
3. Add: lootglitch.me
4. Copy provided values

#### On Domain Registrar:
1. Add CNAME record:
   - Host: @
   - Value: [from Render]
2. Wait for DNS propagation (up to 48 hours)

### 5. Add Real Adsterra Ads

#### In index.html:
Replace placeholder with actual Adsterra code:

```html
<!-- Banner Ad -->
<div class="ad-container banner-ad">
    <!-- Replace this with Adsterra banner code -->
    <script type="text/javascript">
        atOptions = {
            'key' : 'YOUR_BANNER_KEY',
            'format' : 'iframe',
            'height' : 90,
            'width' : 728,
            'params' : {}
        };
    </script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="//www.topcreativeformat.com/YOUR_BANNER_KEY/invoke.js"></script>
</div>
```

#### In app.js:
Update SmartLink function:

```javascript
async showSmartLink() {
    // Replace with actual SmartLink
    const smartLink = 'https://yoursmartlink.com';
    window.open(smartLink, '_blank');
    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));
}
```

### 6. Submit to Google Search Console

#### Setup:
1. Go to [search.google.com/search-console](https://search.google.com/search-console)
2. Add property: lootglitch.me
3. Verify ownership via DNS

#### Submit Sitemap:
1. In Search Console
2. Go to Sitemaps
3. Submit: https://lootglitch.me/sitemap.xml

### 7. Enable Google Analytics (Optional)

Add to `<head>` in index.html:
```html
<!-- Google Analytics -->
<script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-XXXXXXXXXX"></script>
<script>
  window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
  function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
  gtag('js', new Date());
  gtag('config', 'G-XXXXXXXXXX');
</script>
```

## üîÑ Auto-Deploy Setup

### GitHub Actions (Optional)
Create `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`:

```yaml
name: Deploy to Render

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v2
      - name: Trigger Render Deploy
        run: |
          curl https://api.render.com/deploy/YOUR_HOOK_ID
```

## üìä Monitoring

### Check Logs on Render:
1. Go to your service
2. Click "Logs" tab
3. Monitor for errors

### Telegram Admin Commands:
- `/stats` - View statistics
- `/ban username` - Ban user
- `/unban username` - Unban user

## üêõ Troubleshooting

### Site Not Loading:
```bash
# Check build logs on Render
# Verify all environment variables are set
# Check Node.js version compatibility
```

### Telegram Bot Not Working:
```bash
# Verify bot token is correct
# Check admin ID matches your Telegram user ID
# Ensure bot is admin in group
# Check internet connectivity
```

### Database Issues:
```bash
# Verify Telegram group ID is correct
# Check bot has write permissions
# Monitor Telegram messages for errors
```

### Free Tier Sleep:
Render free tier sleeps after 15 minutes of inactivity.

**Solutions:**
1. Upgrade to paid tier ($7/month)
2. Use external ping service:
   - UptimeRobot.com (free)
   - Add your site URL
   - Set interval to 5 minutes

